Hello! I'm glad we're working together to help you create a strong CV. With 20 years of experience as a career consultant, I'm confident that I can guide you through the process.

To get started, could you please provide me with some basic information? Here are some details that I would need:

1. Contact Information: Full name, phone number, and email address.
2. Personal Statement: A brief statement about yourself, your career goals, and what sets you apart from other candidates.
3. Education: Degrees earned, institutions attended, and graduation dates.
4. Work Experience: Job titles, companies, employment dates, and a brief description of your responsibilities and accomplishments at each job.
5. Skills: Technical skills, soft skills, and any certifications you may have.
6. Volunteer Work or Community Involvement: Any unpaid work or volunteer experience that is relevant to your career goals.
7. References: People who can speak to your qualifications and work ethic.

Please take your time to gather this information, and feel free to share it with me in whatever format is most convenient for you â€“ whether that's through email, a Google Doc, or during our call. I'll use this information to help you create a compelling CV that will help you stand out to potential employers.

I look forward to working with you! If you have any questions or need clarification on any of the information I've requested, please don't hesitate to ask.
